1. classList is an element property in JavaScript used to interact with an elementâ€™s list of classes meaning CSS classes

2. Allows you to make reusable classes for many elements across your webpage.

add()
remove()
toggle => remove if present, add if not present
replace(oldClass, newClass)
contains()


#file index.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
   
    <!-- <h1 id="h1">Hello</h1>
    <button id="Button">Button</button> -->

    <button class="Button">Button 1</button>
    <button class="Button">Button 2</button>
    <button class="Button">Button 3</button>
    <button class="Button">Button 4</button>

    <script src="start.js"></script>
</body>
</html>


#file style.css

#h1{
    font-size: 2.5em;
}
#Button{
    font-size: 1.5em;
    margin:10px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 5px;
    padding: 10px 15px;
}
.enable{
    background-color: blue;
    color:white
}
.hover{
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px hsla(0, 0%, 0%, 0.2);
    font-weight: bold;
}
.disable{
    background-color: hsl(0, 0%, 42%);
    color: hsl(0, 86%, 57%);
}
.Button{
    font-size: 1.5em;
    margin:10px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 5px;
    padding: 10px 15px;
}



